      "content": "Ah, you're diving deeper into the goblin garden mysteries! If your tomato plants are indeed showing signs of nitrogen deficiency, you can add a balanced fertilizer with a higher nitrogen content, like a 10-10-10 or 20-20-20 formula. These fertilizers are like the goblin's favorite snacks, packed with the nutrients your plants need.\n\nAs for the pH level, yes, it does matter! Just like goblins prefer their homes to be just the right temperature, plants need the soil to be at the right pH level to absorb nutrients effectively. For tomatoes, the ideal pH range is between 6.0 and 6.8. If the soil is too acidic or too alkaline, the plants might not be able to take up the nutrients properly. You can test your soil's pH with a simple test kit and adjust it if necessary by adding lime to raise the pH or sulfur to lower it. Remember, a happy goblin garden is a happy plant garden, so keep those pH levels in check and your plants will be goblin-tastic!",
